1ï¸âƒ£ What is the Rod Cutting Problem? (Very Simple)

You are given:

A rod of length N

A price list where:

price[i] = price of rod piece of length i

Your task:

ğŸ‘‰ Cut the rod in any way
ğŸ‘‰ Sell the pieces
ğŸ‘‰ Get maximum total profit

ğŸ’¡ You can cut the rod any number of times.

2ï¸âƒ£ Simple Example (Understand First)

Rod length = 4

Piece Length	1	2	3	4
Price        	2	5	7	8

Possible ways:

4 â†’ price = 8

2 + 2 â†’ 5 + 5 = 10 âœ…

1 + 3 â†’ 2 + 7 = 9

1 + 1 + 1 + 1 â†’ 8

ğŸ‘‰ Maximum profit = 10

3ï¸âƒ£ Important Rules / Criteria
âœ… Rule 1: Rod can be cut into any number of pieces

(Unlike 0/1 Knapsack)

âœ… Rule 2: You can use the same length again

(Unbounded problem)

âœ… Rule 3: Order of pieces does NOT matter
âœ… Rule 4: Goal is to maximize total price
4ï¸âƒ£ Why Dynamic Programming?
Brute force problem:

Try all cut combinations âŒ

Exponential time

DP idea:

â€œFor each rod length, store the maximum profit possibleâ€

5ï¸âƒ£ DP Meaning (MOST IMPORTANT)

Let:

dp[i]
Meaning:

Maximum profit obtainable from rod of length i

6ï¸âƒ£ DP Relation (Core Logic)

For rod length i:

Try all possible first cuts:

dp[i] = max(price[j] + dp[i - j])
where j = 1 to i

ğŸ’¡ Meaning:

Cut a piece of length j

Remaining rod = i - j

Add best profit of remaining part

